<DOCNO> AP891102-0009 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a nation that nervously watched the california 
earthquake on television and then sent more than 7 million in aid 
received a scare and a shaking from an equally powerful tremor 
today 
no casualties or major damage were reported in todays quake 
which measured an estimated 71 on the richter scale and whose 
impact was blunted by its epicenters distance from japans pacific 
coast about 80 miles 
nevertheless 6165 people from six coastal towns and villages 
were evacuated to town halls and school gymnasiums for fear of 
tsunami or waves generated by the quake said toshihara kon a 
fire department official in iwate prefecture about 300 miles 
northeast of tokyo 
the evacuation order was lifted 3 hours after the quake hit at 
326 am kon said shortly after that all tsunami warnings were 
lifted the central meteorological agency reported 
as felt in northern honshu japans main island the quake was 
strong enough to shake buildings and topple unstable objects 
waves of up to two feet were reported in some areas and about 
400 boats mostly fishing craft put out to sea from hachinohe to 
avoid being caught in the harbor by tsunami they later returned 
kon said a small landslide briefly blocked traffic on a local 
road but fallen dirt and rocks were cleared and traffic soon 
returned to normal 
officials briefly closed the main expressway through the 
affected region for inspection and overnight trains were stopped so 
rails could be inspected 
japans meteorological agency estimated the quakes magnitude at 
71 on the richter scale nearly the same as that of the quake that 
devastated much of the san francisco bay area on oct 17 
the us geological survey in colorado estimated the japanese 
quakes magnitude at 73 don finley a spokesman for the survey 
said it was the strongest in the region since a 77 quake on march 
9 1931 
toshio akiyama head of the japanese agencys earthquake and 
tsunami observation division said that although distance weakened 
the effect of todays quake authorities were concerned because a 
series of quakes have occurred in the area in recent months 
on sunday a quake registering 65 and centered about 95 miles 
off the coast hit the area without causing casualties or damage 
like california japan sits atop a major fault and is frequently 
shaken by earthquakes although few cause casualties fears of a 
major temblor prompt regular national disasterprevention drills 
and newer buildings are designed to withstand quakes of up to 8 on 
the richter scale 
many japanese had immediate word of the san francisco quake as 
they tuned in for a satellite telecast of the world series 
the foreign ministry said it knew of at least 72 million in 
government and private contributions from japan for san francisco 
quake victims 
after that quake japanese experts rushed to the area hoping to 
learn why some buildings collapsed and others stood 
akiyama said japan had a second quake today at 457 am in 
tottori prefecture about 300 miles southwest of tokyo he said 
there were no casualties or damage reported from that 57magnitude 
quake and todays two temblors were not related 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph a quake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage in 
populated areas and a quake of 7 is capable of widespread heavy 
damage 
</TEXT>
