an awesome aftershock to the 
devastating oct 17 earthquake jolted northern california late 
wednesday panicking people from san francisco to watsonville 
the tremor caused some minor damage but there were no immediate 
reports of injuries 
the aftershock hit shortly before 10 pm and was felt in san 
francisco santa cruz and watsonville 
it rattled pretty good at first and then kept on kind of 
rolling you could feel the foundation swaying said ani 
leritzmurphy of watsonville 
the 950 pm aftershock measured 44 on the richter scale of 
ground motion and was centered slightly north of the epicenter of 
last months magnitude71 quake said pat jorgenson spokeswoman 
for the us geological survey in menlo park 
