the house wants to give the transportation 
secretary new authority to halt airline mergers or leverage buyouts 
even though the secretary says he doesnt need more power 
the house on wednesday passed 300113 a bill to require 
government rejection of any airline takeover that might affect 
safety hinder competition cut a carriers size affect jobs or 
result in foreign control of an airline 
under the legislation which now goes to the senate the 
secretary is to determine whether transactions meet the standards 
before they are completed but he also will have the power to 
approve any merger if he believes it is in the public interest 
current law calls for a department review of airline 
acquisitions after they have been completed and based only on 
considerations of safety financial fitness and foreign control 
transportation secretary samuel skinner says he doesnt want the 
new authority and would recommend a presidential veto the vote 
exceeded the twothirds majority necessary to override a veto 
the house added two amendments which are opposed by democrat and 
republican leaders of the public works committee 
one change extended the authority to cover any takeover that 
would reduce wages benefits or the number of employees at the 
affected airline opponents said this would be interference in 
managementemployee relations 
another change aimed at texas air corp owner frank lorenzo 
would bar anyone who has sent more than one airline into bankruptcy 
from acquiring another airline lorenzo has filed for bankruptcy 
reorganization of eastern airlines and took a similar step with 
continental airlines 
the bill was prompted by increasing concern over leveraged 
buyouts in the airline industry including the sale of northwest 
