money to support research on fetal tissue from induced abortions 
for moral reasons saying it could lead to more abortions 
ultimately he said society would have to trade off the rights 
of a fetus for those of a patient suffering from parkinsons 
disease or other condition that might benefit from fetal tissue 
even those that strongly favor fetal tissue transplantation 
acknowledge that a strict wall would have to be erected between the 
abortion decision and the decision to use fetal tissue in 
transplantation research mason said such a distinction is 
easy to theorize but i just dont believe that such a neat 
separation can be accomplished 
for anyone who believes that a fetus has some rights then i 
just find that this is unacceptable public policy he said 
