<TEXT>
the us embassy has issued its fourth protest in 
a week over a massive chinese police presence outside its compound 
and the harassment by guards of staff and visitors an embassy 
source said today 
also today china said the visit of former president nixon will 
help restore badly strained relations with the united states but 
insisted again that the blame for the strain lies with washington 
the embassy source speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
latest verbal protest came wednesday hours before another night of 
provocations outside ambassador james lilleys residence 
on wednesday night about two dozen uniformed police and at 
least 10 plainclothes police congregated outside the gate to the 
residence shining a spotlight and forcing visitors to go through a 
gauntlet of armed guards 
another 20 policemen were posted on nearby streetcorners and 
along the street in front of the compound turning some cars away 
and forcing those going to the embassy to park hundreds of yards 
away even though there were many empty spaces near the gate 
when visitors tried to park closer to the embassy police banged 
on their cars and yelled at them to leave 
police cursed at a cbs crew that tried to film them and shined 
another spotlight into the crews camera 
a similar massing of police occurred tuesday evening only then 
they were armed with automatic rifles and did not carry spotlights 
in an apparent gesture to nixon the peoples armed police 
around the three american embassy compounds did not carry rifles 
wednesday for the first time in four months 
nixon aides said the former president told premier li peng he 
did not like guns and did not want to see rifletoting guards when 
he visited the embassy 
today guards continued to wear pistols and eight black or gray 
mercedes some without license plates were again parked along the 
street outside the ambassadors residence with men apparently 
plainclothes police seated inside 
the embassy also has complained of three cases of embassy staff 
finding their car tires slashed and security forces tailing embassy 
employees as they left the compounds 
twice in the past week armed police outside the embassy pointed 
their automatic rifles at children of us diplomats and pulled the 
trigger an embassy source said the guns were not loaded 
the only unusual event at the embassy recently was a halloween 
party last saturday where the arrival of people wearing costumes 
apparently rattled the chinese 
at least 80 police were called in seemingly to block chinese 
fugitives from sneaking into embassy grounds police became 
particularly upset when partygoers arrived carrying a fake coffin 
one man who came to the party dressed in a gorilla suit was told 
to park his car elsewhere 
premier li reportedly told nixon that the heavy guard most 
embassies have only one or two chinese police posted outside was 
necessary to prevent the escape of dissidents fang lizhi and his 
wife li shuxian who took refuge in the embassy after the june 4 
military crackdown on the prodemocracy movement 
fang and li wanted by chinese police as counterrevolutionary 
agitators remain in one of the embassy compounds 
foreign ministry spokesman li zhaoxing asked about the police 
harassment at a weekly briefing today said china always attached 
importance to the safety of the foreign embassies in china 
li said nixons fiveday visit which ended several before the 
briefing will undoubtedly be conducive to the restoration and 
development of the normal relations 
but he said it is imperative for the united states and 
actually the united states only to take the initiative in 
improving ties 
washington cut off highlevel contacts with beijing after the 
crackdown when chinese troops killed hundreds of unarmed 
civilians it has urged china to end repression against those who 
advocate democratic reform 
nixon aides said the former president will present a written 
account of his private visit to president bush 
