conservative government 
share prices tumbled in early trading but recovered later amid 
the rumors that a cabinet minister was about to quit prime minister 
margaret thatchers government because of the alleged scandal 
the jittery market reaction and the speculation that parkinson 
was involved reflected edginess about the government 
it already was shaken by last weeks resignation of chancellor 
of the exchequer nigel lawson in a policy dispute with mrs 
thatcher 
in the first hour of trading the financial timesstock exchange 
