senators made clear thursday they want house 
members to join them in disclosing mass mailing costs but refused 
to force the issue in order to avoid scuttling a deal to cut the 
taxpayerfinanced mailings in half 
senators voted 6435 to table in effect to reject an 
amendment by sen gordon humphrey rnh that would have required 
the house disclosure 
sen harry reid dnev warned that the house would reject a 
conference agreement to cut mass mailings from six to three 
annually per member if senators attempted to change house rules 
reid the chief senate negotiator of the mail reduction 
agreement said that while he and other senators fought earlier for 
humphreys plan for quarterly disclosure they were unwilling to 
jeopardize the compromise now 
we have gotten from the house all were going to get said 
reid the conference we had with the house was brutal the house 
had the feeling we should clean up our house before we tell them 
what to do 
humphrey however argued we have to say were not going to 
