<TEXT>
wearing the bishops mitre in the roman catholic church in the 
united states has never been easy 
from the day in 1789 when pope pius vi established the diocese 
of baltimore and named john carroll the first us catholic bishop 
the church here has had to defend the american way of life before 
the holy see and to calm the fears of noncatholics that it was 
controlled by a foreign power 
as its bishops meet in baltimore this week to celebrate the 
bicentennial of the catholic hierarchy in the united states with a 
conservative pope seeking greater central authority and the 
abortion battle fueling critics claims that the church wants to 
set moral standards for the nation the church is still trying to 
find its place in the american experiment in democracy 
i think the current leadership of the us catholic conference 
needs to continue to articulate to the holy see the unique 
characteristics of the united states said bishop james malone of 
