kid on the block 
the 53 millionmember catholic church in the united states has 
grown from a persecuted minority in an isolated outpost to the 
nations largest religious group and one of the most influential 
voices of catholicism in the world 
if a pope today tried to correct the errors of americanism 
with a scolding papal encyclical as pope leo xiii did in 1899 
it just wont be paid attention to said jay dolan a historian 
at notre dame 
the united states revolutionary experiment in democracy made 
its mark on the catholic hierarchy from the start 
heeding pleas from 18th century jesuit missionaries such as 
