labor and urged minimum wage laws and other social reforms was 
published that year catholics in other nations didnt begin this 
sort of activism until the 1950s 
the church in the united states was very conscious of the way 
the us was organized politically said monsignor joesph 
gremillion a scholarinresidence at notre dame the church 
leadership in the united states felt the need of comparing notes 
consulting with one another taking positions 
the catholic conference in this country became a model for 
national and regional church groups elsewhere after the 196165 
second vatican council gave official recognition to national 
conferences the national conference of catholic bishops was formed 
in 1966 
the vatican however may not have been ready for the influence 
wielded by the us bishops 
