just 2 percent of the crop planted compared to an average of 11 
percent for the same date in recent years 
brazil is the worlds secondlargest soybean producer after the 
united states analysts say economic troubles are forcing south 
american farmers to reduce their plantings of both soybeans and 
corn 
indications of new export business supported the soybean and 
wheat markets news of soviet interest in buying us meat has 
spurred speculation that the soviet union may increase its imports 
of other commodites too 
