<TEXT>
mobil oil co announced plans thursday to spend 
468 million building a north sea gas pipeline and onshore 
processing plant at st fergus in northeast scotland 
a statement by the company said the project is expected to 
create 700 construction jobs the processing plant will have a 
permanent staff of 80 when in production in three years 
mobil said the 210mile pipeline will carry gas to the plant 
from mobils beryl oil field in the oil and gasrich north sea 
gas is an important secondary product from north sea oil production 
the plant will sell 90 percent of the beryl fields gas output 
to british gas plc the formerly stateowned company that has a 
nearmonopoly in supplying gas to britains industries and homes 
through its nationwide pipeline system 
the statement said the remaining 10 percent of the gas will be 
sold by mobil itself directly to industry 
mobil said the plant will have an output of 250000 cubic feet a 
day it said the pipeline and plant will also be able to 
accommodate gas from the brae field in the north sea 
</TEXT>
